
# title: Summary, imperative, use lower case commit tag, start upper case, don't end with a period
# ex. update: Rename modules directory
# No more than 50 chars. ### 50th char is here:  #

# Leave blank line between subject and body
# Body: Explain *what* and *why* (not *how*)
# Wrap at 72 chars. ################################## which is here:  #
|What:
# What functionality changed

|Why:
# Why the change was made

# commit tags:
#   -add: generic tag for adding anything to a repo
#   -implement: adding framework, library, or other established code
#   -update: any changes to existing material that is not the codebase (assets, etc)
#   -fix: quick fixes (1-3 lines)
#   -bug: larger bug fixes (3+ lines or entire files)
#   -remove: generic tag for removing anything from a repo
#   -feat: implementing a new feature
#   -refactor: refactoring part of the established code base
#   -docs: changes to the documentation
